An overview of the role of communication management in an organisation. Identification of stakeholders and their communication needs, analysis of cases, and application of the methods of communication management.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop an understanding of the importance of communication management in the work of an organisation. To develop a skill to distinguish between stakeholders and their communication needs, to solve communication problems and apply the methods of communication management.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course: - understands the importance of communication management in an organisation; - is able to identify the stakeholders of organisation and their communication needs; - is able to analyse the cases related to communication management; - is able to apply the methods of communication management.
